escribe the calcium hypothesis of AD, which is gaining popularity. We present data supporting this hypothesis and focus on a recently discovered calcium-signaling pathway that is dysregulated in AD and propose targets for the development of disease-modifying therapies.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Попугаева","given":"Елена","literal":""},{"family":"Popugaeva","given":"Elena","literal":""},{"family":"Власова","given":"О. Л.","literal":""},{"family":"Vlasova","given":"O. L.","literal":""},{"family":"Bezprozvanny","given":"Ilya","literal":""},{"family":"Bezprozvanny","given":"Ilya","literal":""}],"citation-key":"_restoring_2015","year":"2015","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Restoring calcium homeostasis to treat Alzheimer's disease: a future perspective"],"author-links":["[[Author/Елена Попугаева]]","[[Author/Elena Popugaeva]]","[[Author/О. Л. Власова]]","[[Author/O. L. Vlasova]]","[[Author/Ilya Bezprozvanny]]","[[Author/Ilya Bezprozvanny]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/_restoring_2015/_restoring_2015.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"qzunnb","at":1774951888951}},"smart_blocks:Research/@_restoring_2015.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.03347164,-0.01723438,0.06976863,0.00032966,-0.02574369,-0.02360955,-0.04048181,0.07298774,0.02691675,-0.03499303,0.00435362,-0.07862778,0.03680129,0.11126383,-0.00368512,0.02157284,-0.04875682,0.03763845,-0.04435471,0.03274793,0.03415775,-0.07910591,0.02420923,0.02255163,0.04241411,0.04827771,0.01058324,0.02755667,-0.04538037,-0.21018161,-0.06251294,-0.01712329,0.01869692,-0.02434063,-0.02552841,0.01797772,-0.02347963,0.04521673,-0.03878485,0.04549846,0.0228182,0.01291803,0.00160833,-0.01832514,-0.00129089,-0.01758368,-0.06084282,-0.03758145,-0.01647213,0.00209348,0.00133316,0.05715203,-0.03668664,0.06586396,0.00726628,0.06114218,0.00472867,0.04501203,0.03926603,0.09544518,